  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (adversarial INT-1)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). This package embeds compound weakness COMPOUND-01: the bound claim carries no prov:wasDerivedFrom provenance link (W-EP-01, Critical) and the primary validation result omits hasUncertaintyQuantification (W-AL-01, High).",
