    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors appropriately scoped out per ASME V&V 40 Table 3 guidance for Class II device at MRL 2. Primary validation demonstrates mean NIH error of 8.3% against FDA benchmark experimental data, satisfying the 15% acceptance criterion. GCI study confirms mesh-independent solution. Model form and input uncertainty analyses support robustness of CFD predictions. COU decision to accept CFD results for identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions is supported by the credibility evidence assembled.",
